1
00:00:45,254 --> 00:00:48,966
PERFECT CROWN

2
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:00,978
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

3
00:01:01,061 --> 00:01:02,980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:01:03,647 --> 00:01:04,648
EPISODE 11

5
00:01:05,816 --> 00:01:08,110
Your Royal Highness,
it is the Queen Mother.

6
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:18,036
I'd like a brief audience
in the Council Hall.

7
00:01:18,120 --> 00:01:20,372
Do we have time
before we're due at the Throne Hall?

8
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:21,832
Well…

9
00:01:22,833 --> 00:01:25,252
Yes, we have about 30 minutes.

10
00:01:26,128 --> 00:01:27,337
Right.

11
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:33,885
Your Royal Highness.

12
00:01:35,137 --> 00:01:38,724
It seems like His Majesty wants to enter
the Throne Hall with you?

13
00:01:38,807 --> 00:01:39,808
His Majesty does?

14
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:41,852
Yes. It appears he's a bit nervous.

15
00:01:45,856 --> 00:01:46,857
I'll meet you there.

16
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,442
I won't be long.

17
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:50,610
Ah…

18
00:01:55,157 --> 00:01:56,491
Yes, Your Royal Highness.

19
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:30,275
Grand Princess.

20
00:02:30,901 --> 00:02:31,902
You must flee.

21
00:02:32,653 --> 00:02:35,447
Isn't that… the Council Hall?

22
00:02:36,239 --> 00:02:37,324
Grand Princess.

23
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:50,170
No…

24
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:53,799
No!

25
00:02:53,882 --> 00:02:55,050
Your Highness!

26
00:03:03,225 --> 00:03:04,768
What was that?

27
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:08,397
Go and see what happened.

28
00:03:09,606 --> 00:03:10,899
Yes, Your Majesty.

29
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:35,632
Aide Do.

30
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:36,925
What…

31
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,262
What are you doing here?

32
00:03:46,601 --> 00:03:47,811
Tell me.

33
00:03:51,481 --> 00:03:52,732
Do Hyejeong!

34
00:03:52,816 --> 00:03:54,192
The Council Hall…

35
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:58,280
His Royal Highness.

36
00:03:59,322 --> 00:04:01,408
He's in the Council Hall.

37
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:21,928
Your Royal Highness.

38
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:25,974
No!

39
00:04:26,057 --> 00:04:27,684
-Grand Princess!
-Ms. Seong!

40
00:04:28,602 --> 00:04:30,312
You can't, Grand Princess!

41
00:04:39,362 --> 00:04:41,990
PERFECT CROWN

42
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:55,712
Is anyone…

43
00:04:55,796 --> 00:04:57,380
Is anyone out there?

44
00:04:57,464 --> 00:04:59,800
Your Royal Highness!

45
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:13,438
Your Royal Highness!

46
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:15,398
Your Royal Highness!

47
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:27,702
If something terrible happens to you…

48
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:30,956
You can't…

49
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:37,087
Let's see this through.

50
00:05:40,924 --> 00:05:42,467
I will be by your side.

51
00:05:53,478 --> 00:05:54,479
Don't come.

52
00:05:56,064 --> 00:05:57,065
Your Royal Highness!

53
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:07,242
Your Royal Highness!

54
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,036
Your Royal Highness…

55
00:06:19,963 --> 00:06:21,047
Your Royal Highness.

56
00:06:22,257 --> 00:06:23,258
Your Royal Highness!

57
00:06:30,765 --> 00:06:32,684
Your Royal Highness.

58
00:06:34,019 --> 00:06:35,186
Your Royal Highness.

59
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:37,480
Your Royal Highness, you need to wake up.

60
00:06:47,032 --> 00:06:48,199
Your Royal Highness.

61
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:05,842
Your Royal Highness.

62
00:07:07,844 --> 00:07:09,679
I'll get you out of here.

63
00:07:32,535 --> 00:07:33,536
Your Royal Highness.

64
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,790
Your Royal Highness, please wake up.

65
00:07:40,418 --> 00:07:42,545
Someone, please save him.

66
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:45,090
Is anyone out there?

67
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:48,510
Is there anyone out there?

68
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:57,268
Please help us…

69
00:07:59,062 --> 00:08:00,063
Your Royal Highness.

70
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:02,273
Your Royal Highness…

71
00:08:06,778 --> 00:08:08,029
Mother!

72
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:09,531
Your Majesty.

73
00:08:10,031 --> 00:08:12,909
Mother, there's a fire in the palace.

74
00:08:13,868 --> 00:08:15,203
What is he talking about?

75
00:08:15,787 --> 00:08:17,789
A fire has broken out at the Council Hall.

76
00:08:18,415 --> 00:08:20,750
Uncle is…

77
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,049
Is I-AN safe?

78
00:08:28,717 --> 00:08:29,801
Your Majesty…

79
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,137
Answer me!

80
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,472
Is I-AN safe?

81
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:54,367
You should get some rest, Grand Princess.

82
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,203
The royal physicians said he is stable.

83
00:08:58,788 --> 00:09:02,375
How could you have just run
into the fire like that?

84
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:04,461
Had Aide Choi not reached you in time,

85
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,670
you would also be…

86
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:07,464
He would've come to save me.

87
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:09,883
Pardon?

88
00:09:11,843 --> 00:09:15,055
If it had been me in there, he would have…

89
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:20,977
come for me too.

90
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:23,354
To save me.

91
00:09:26,483 --> 00:09:28,109
Like he always has.

92
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:38,161
Sir, you need to be announced first! Ah…

93
00:09:51,716 --> 00:09:53,426
The Grand Prince is stable, so tomorrow--

94
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:55,386
How could you just run in there like that?

95
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,891
Lower your voice.
The palace attendants are outside.

96
00:09:59,974 --> 00:10:01,309
Why aren't you at a hospital?

97
00:10:02,477 --> 00:10:04,979
You should at least get proper treatment.

98
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:07,857
How can I trust any hospital right now?

99
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,318
-What?
-You think this fire was just an accident?

100
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:15,490
They targeted the Grand Prince
at the wedding, not me.

101
00:10:15,573 --> 00:10:17,826
And now, a fire just breaks out
on abdication day?

102
00:10:17,909 --> 00:10:19,077
You expect me to buy that?

103
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:24,582
And if it wasn't an accident?

104
00:10:26,501 --> 00:10:28,920
-What?
-What can you do if it wasn't?

105
00:10:29,838 --> 00:10:32,757
Will you collapse and die in his place?

106
00:10:33,925 --> 00:10:36,052
Then what should I have done?

107
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:38,596
-Just leave him there to die?
-Yes, just leave him!

108
00:10:41,516 --> 00:10:42,851
Jeongwoo.

109
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:51,067
How much longer
must I watch you be in danger?

110
00:10:55,780 --> 00:10:57,574
How much longer must I endure this?

111
00:11:21,181 --> 00:11:22,974
I've been looking everywhere for you.

112
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,435
What are you doing here?

113
00:11:32,442 --> 00:11:33,484
Are you okay?

114
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:37,989
Yes.

115
00:11:39,949 --> 00:11:42,744
I'm told the Grand Prince
and Princess are both fine.

116
00:11:42,827 --> 00:11:44,579
You don't need to worry too much.

117
00:11:53,254 --> 00:11:55,757
I'm sorry.

118
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,218
What? Why are you apologizing?

119
00:12:00,303 --> 00:12:01,304
I mean…

120
00:12:04,599 --> 00:12:07,185
I should've never left
the Grand Prince's side, right?

121
00:12:07,268 --> 00:12:08,603
Wait, come on now.

122
00:12:08,686 --> 00:12:11,356
It's not like your being there

123
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:13,608
would've magically stopped
the fire from starting.

124
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:15,360
Come on, that's silly.

125
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:24,994
Wait, hold on. Do you really believe that?

126
00:12:38,549 --> 00:12:39,634
Thank you.

127
00:12:40,343 --> 00:12:41,344
What?

128
00:12:42,637 --> 00:12:44,222
-Grand Princess!
-Ms. Seong!

129
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:45,848
You can't, Grand Princess!

130
00:12:53,856 --> 00:12:54,857
I'll be right back.

131
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:56,359
What? Where are you going?

132
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,860
No, you can't!

133
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:00,613
Aide Choi! Choi Hyeon!

134
00:13:11,749 --> 00:13:12,792
A royal physician!

135
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:14,294
Summon a royal physician!

136
00:13:20,717 --> 00:13:21,843
Thank goodness…

137
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,053
Thank goodness.

138
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:32,353
If it weren't for you, they would both be…

139
00:13:32,437 --> 00:13:33,438
Oh.

140
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,773
Stop that.

141
00:13:35,857 --> 00:13:38,443
I mean, I was just doing my job.

142
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:48,703
I was worried…

143
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:51,873
that you'd get hurt.

144
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:17,440
Thank you.

145
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:20,610
But you know,

146
00:14:21,194 --> 00:14:22,528
I just got all better.

147
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:27,825
Oh, ow, ow… Hold on. Ow…

148
00:14:27,909 --> 00:14:29,202
Are you okay?

149
00:14:30,036 --> 00:14:32,497
It's so itchy right here.
Can you scratch it for me?

150
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:35,708
Why are you crying?

151
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:36,918
Don't cry.

152
00:14:37,001 --> 00:14:39,462
Crying one second and laughing the next?

153
00:14:40,046 --> 00:14:41,881
Just pick one already.

154
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,216
You're no crybaby.

155
00:14:43,299 --> 00:14:45,510
Where are all these tears coming from?
Huh?

156
00:14:55,311 --> 00:14:56,938
What's wrong? Are you feeling unwell?

157
00:14:57,021 --> 00:14:58,731
Should we go to the hospital?

158
00:14:58,815 --> 00:14:59,816
Why was he…

159
00:15:01,275 --> 00:15:03,152
at the Council Hall today?

160
00:15:03,236 --> 00:15:05,446
He was due to accept
the abdication in the Throne Hall.

161
00:15:06,239 --> 00:15:07,240
Oh…

162
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:10,159
Prime Minister Min texted,
asking for a quick chat

163
00:15:10,243 --> 00:15:11,410
at the Council Hall.

164
00:15:14,664 --> 00:15:15,915
Jeongwoo…

165
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,668
had him go there?

166
00:15:20,545 --> 00:15:21,754
Yes.

167
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:52,702
Your Royal Highness.

168
00:15:54,745 --> 00:15:56,164
Your Royal Highness!

169
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:09,468
Stay still.

170
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:22,857
I must appear…

171
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,610
insanely infatuated with you

172
00:16:26,903 --> 00:16:28,321
for people to believe

173
00:16:29,614 --> 00:16:31,324
this absurd marriage is genuine.

174
00:16:34,202 --> 00:16:35,453
Do not bend to their will.

175
00:16:37,163 --> 00:16:38,247
Do not back away

176
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,292
and do not compromise.

177
00:16:46,047 --> 00:16:47,757
I shall fight with all that I have.

178
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:53,095
Just as you do.

179
00:16:57,183 --> 00:16:59,352
I have a great deal that you do not…

180
00:17:00,770 --> 00:17:02,521
and if you ask for it,

181
00:17:03,898 --> 00:17:05,608
I fully intend to provide it.

182
00:17:50,570 --> 00:17:53,239
I thought you said
the palace was the safest.

183
00:17:57,285 --> 00:18:00,121
Is there any place safe for you?

184
00:18:15,886 --> 00:18:18,347
The Council Hall was
practically empty at the time.

185
00:18:18,431 --> 00:18:20,641
For an explosion that big,
casualties are minimal.

186
00:18:21,392 --> 00:18:24,061
We will make a joint statement
with the Royal Secretariat--

187
00:18:24,145 --> 00:18:25,438
No need.

188
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:27,898
Just leave it for now.

189
00:18:28,566 --> 00:18:29,734
Pardon?

190
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:32,695
Let's leave it until the Grand Prince…

191
00:18:34,196 --> 00:18:35,364
wakes up.

192
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:42,538
Last night, a major fire broke out
at Gyeongbokgung Palace.

193
00:18:42,622 --> 00:18:47,668
Witnesses at Gwanghwamun Square
reported hearing a loud explosion.

194
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:50,212
With no official statement
from the palace yet,

195
00:18:50,296 --> 00:18:53,257
there are growing concerns
over the safety of the royal family.

196
00:18:53,341 --> 00:18:55,343
I want the past month's CCTV footage

197
00:18:55,426 --> 00:18:57,720
of the Council Hall interior,
entrance, and corridors.

198
00:18:57,803 --> 00:18:59,096
Have it copied and sent over.

199
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:00,806
Is three days enough to review?

200
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:05,811
With Court Lady Choi, Aide Choi,

201
00:19:05,895 --> 00:19:08,522
and Castle Beauty's Exec Ops on board,

202
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:10,066
we'll make it happen.

203
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:13,653
I want to question every attendant,
Royal Guard, and official

204
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:16,989
in the vicinity of the Council Hall
at the time of the incident.

205
00:19:17,073 --> 00:19:20,159
Uh, that would fall
under the Inner Court's jurisdiction.

206
00:19:20,242 --> 00:19:21,285
Mmm…

207
00:19:21,369 --> 00:19:23,829
I'll ask for cooperation
from the Queen Mother's Quarters.

208
00:19:25,748 --> 00:19:26,749
No need.

209
00:19:27,917 --> 00:19:30,086
I'll just ask her myself.

210
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:39,804
Is I-AN all right?

211
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:45,017
I wanted to visit him
at Anhwadang Hall, but…

212
00:19:45,101 --> 00:19:46,519
Worried that he might actually…

213
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:49,313
pull through?

214
00:19:52,650 --> 00:19:55,069
It happened as he was
about to accept the abdication.

215
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,655
And Your Majesty was the only one

216
00:19:58,280 --> 00:19:59,740
who was against it.

217
00:20:01,617 --> 00:20:03,202
Grand Princess, I…

218
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:05,204
If you don't want to be a suspect,

219
00:20:05,788 --> 00:20:07,206
grant me unfettered access

220
00:20:08,332 --> 00:20:10,501
to the palace attendants' shift records.

221
00:20:16,173 --> 00:20:18,300
His Royal Highness will pull through.

222
00:20:22,179 --> 00:20:23,180
That's the only way…

223
00:20:32,356 --> 00:20:34,692
you make it out of this unscathed.

224
00:20:39,947 --> 00:20:40,948
Oh…

225
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:44,744
I'm afraid I don't accept drinks
so freely anymore.

226
00:20:57,298 --> 00:20:58,299
And the investigation?

227
00:20:58,799 --> 00:20:59,842
When will it begin?

228
00:20:59,925 --> 00:21:02,094
The Royal Protection Branch
will start it first,

229
00:21:02,178 --> 00:21:04,263
and the police will join later.

230
00:21:04,346 --> 00:21:05,389
It will not be public.

231
00:21:06,557 --> 00:21:07,558
Why not public?

232
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:10,478
It came from the prime minister.

233
00:21:10,561 --> 00:21:14,023
With the poisoning case still open,
he wanted to keep things from escalating.

234
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,691
He should be at Anhwadang Hall now.

235
00:21:17,193 --> 00:21:18,277
Who?

236
00:21:18,986 --> 00:21:21,113
-Prime Minister Min?
-Yes.

237
00:21:33,209 --> 00:21:34,210
Did you run over here?

238
00:21:39,131 --> 00:21:40,966
He should've been awake by now,

239
00:21:41,050 --> 00:21:42,551
but I hadn't heard anything yet.

240
00:21:44,512 --> 00:21:45,721
Right.

241
00:21:45,805 --> 00:21:49,225
The royal physician said he's
in a near-comatose state due to stress.

242
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:52,520
It's a sign his body is recovering,
so he should be waking up soon.

243
00:21:53,938 --> 00:21:54,939
When is "soon"?

244
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:57,525
Well, that is…

245
00:21:57,608 --> 00:22:00,069
Apparently, there's no way of knowing.

246
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:03,489
Let's give it some time.

247
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:14,583
You didn't need to see me out.

248
00:22:16,627 --> 00:22:17,628
Sorry.

249
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,800
Maybe it's everything
that's been going on.

250
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:25,344
I'm a little on edge.

251
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:32,726
By the way, don't you go
to the cathedral anymore?

252
00:22:34,019 --> 00:22:35,020
What?

253
00:22:35,938 --> 00:22:37,356
You're not wearing your rosary.

254
00:22:39,650 --> 00:22:41,235
Ah…

255
00:22:41,318 --> 00:22:42,945
It gets in the way when I work.

256
00:22:43,445 --> 00:22:44,822
Right.

257
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:49,910
Get back safely.

258
00:22:50,870 --> 00:22:52,246
Thanks.

259
00:23:19,273 --> 00:23:20,274
What's wrong?

260
00:23:20,357 --> 00:23:22,610
Huiju hasn't texted back yet?

261
00:23:23,235 --> 00:23:24,236
No.

262
00:23:24,778 --> 00:23:26,655
Let's eat.

263
00:23:27,489 --> 00:23:28,574
What should we get?

264
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:30,868
This place is known for…

265
00:23:30,951 --> 00:23:32,620
-At the palace?
-Yeah.

266
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,663
Someone definitely died there.

267
00:23:35,539 --> 00:23:38,834
Why else would they refuse
to make an official statement?

268
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:39,919
No way.

269
00:23:40,002 --> 00:23:41,754
I did hear the explosion was really loud.

270
00:23:41,837 --> 00:23:43,756
I read this rumor post…

271
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:46,050
It said Grand Prince I-AN…

272
00:23:47,593 --> 00:23:48,844
is dead.

273
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:50,137
Oh, this…

274
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:55,476
-Babe, you need to call Huiju now.
-Okay.

275
00:24:05,110 --> 00:24:07,363
Would it kill her to pick up
on the first try?

276
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:09,657
-She's not picking up? Let me try.
-Okay.

277
00:24:10,157 --> 00:24:13,494
INCOMING CALL
GREMLIN

278
00:24:26,507 --> 00:24:27,508
Sir.

279
00:24:28,759 --> 00:24:30,344
I'm a little tired today.

280
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:31,720
Can we save it for tomorrow?

281
00:24:33,138 --> 00:24:35,933
The Royal Secretariat wants
to release a statement.

282
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:42,147
The reason being?

283
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:45,109
There's a rumor circulating
that the Grand Prince has passed away.

284
00:24:45,192 --> 00:24:48,445
The string of canceled public appearances
has also raised concerns.

285
00:24:48,529 --> 00:24:51,240
There's even talk
the Grand Princess is in a critical state.

286
00:24:51,323 --> 00:24:52,783
Hmm…

287
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:53,867
That should be

288
00:24:54,785 --> 00:24:55,786
more than enough.

289
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:08,215
What on earth are you talking about?

290
00:25:09,508 --> 00:25:10,676
What do you mean, regency?

291
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:13,220
Public concern is growing
over the welfare of the Crown.

292
00:25:14,304 --> 00:25:16,849
However, His Majesty is unable
to carry out state affairs.

293
00:25:16,932 --> 00:25:19,018
Since the Grand Prince
remains unconscious,

294
00:25:19,101 --> 00:25:22,688
it would only be fitting
for Your Majesty to step forward.

295
00:25:22,771 --> 00:25:24,773
The Grand Prince will wake up soon.

296
00:25:25,315 --> 00:25:27,026
-The Grand Princess said--
-That is why

297
00:25:27,109 --> 00:25:29,028
I have come here in such a hurry.

298
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:36,285
Ending the Grand Prince's regency
was no simple matter.

299
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:39,413
Likewise, once Your Majesty
takes up the regency,

300
00:25:39,496 --> 00:25:41,123
it will not be easily undone.

301
00:25:41,206 --> 00:25:42,791
Even if the Grand Prince wakes up.

302
00:25:42,875 --> 00:25:44,877
That would be a rash decision.

303
00:25:45,836 --> 00:25:47,504
-There is still time--
-Your Majesty.

304
00:25:51,467 --> 00:25:53,218
If the notion bothers you so…

305
00:25:53,844 --> 00:25:57,473
"Fulfill your duties to the Crown
as a representative of the people."

306
00:25:59,391 --> 00:26:00,934
I can make it an official order.

307
00:26:07,524 --> 00:26:08,567
So what will it be?

308
00:26:18,035 --> 00:26:19,328
Your Majesty.

309
00:26:19,870 --> 00:26:21,663
Grand Prince I-AN has arrived.

310
00:26:37,638 --> 00:26:38,889
I-AN…

311
00:26:43,310 --> 00:26:46,355
Please forgive me
for causing you concern, Your Majesty.

312
00:26:52,111 --> 00:26:53,112
Did I…

313
00:26:55,823 --> 00:26:56,990
cause you much distress?

314
00:27:08,585 --> 00:27:11,380
SAJEONGJEON HALL WEST ENTRANCE
ACCESS LOG

315
00:27:12,881 --> 00:27:15,968
I expected there would be a lot,

316
00:27:16,051 --> 00:27:17,177
but this is unreal.

317
00:27:17,261 --> 00:27:18,679
Even if it's extensive,

318
00:27:19,429 --> 00:27:23,308
attendants follow a strict routine,
so any irregularities will stand out.

319
00:27:24,518 --> 00:27:26,645
Plus, only a few
have access to the Council Hall.

320
00:27:26,728 --> 00:27:27,729
Right.

321
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:29,481
Your Royal Highness!

322
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:34,278
The Grand Prince is awake!

323
00:27:35,070 --> 00:27:36,154
Your Royal Highness!

324
00:28:37,049 --> 00:28:38,383
You shouldn't have been there.

325
00:28:40,177 --> 00:28:42,387
If something happened to you…

326
00:28:47,851 --> 00:28:49,561
How could I possibly stay out…

327
00:28:51,647 --> 00:28:54,608
…when I knew you were in there?

328
00:29:04,034 --> 00:29:05,035
I'm sorry.

329
00:29:07,079 --> 00:29:08,121
Forgive me.

330
00:29:54,584 --> 00:29:56,294
When did you wake up?

331
00:29:57,087 --> 00:29:58,088
Just now.

332
00:29:59,172 --> 00:30:00,841
Have you seen the royal physician?

333
00:30:03,385 --> 00:30:04,928
It was just a long nap.

334
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:06,013
He says I'm fine.

335
00:30:10,559 --> 00:30:12,853
I'll resume my public duties at once.

336
00:30:12,936 --> 00:30:13,937
Don't worry.

337
00:30:14,021 --> 00:30:16,857
First, we should let you fully recover.

338
00:30:16,940 --> 00:30:17,941
Prime Minister Min.

339
00:30:19,317 --> 00:30:22,112
I hear rumors of my passing
are spreading outside these walls.

340
00:30:26,867 --> 00:30:28,118
Now is the perfect time

341
00:30:29,286 --> 00:30:30,537
to turn public opinion.

342
00:30:59,107 --> 00:31:01,109
Since the Grand Prince
has regained consciousness,

343
00:31:02,611 --> 00:31:04,362
it's time we tied up some loose ends.

344
00:31:09,659 --> 00:31:12,370
LORD INPYEONG

345
00:31:51,326 --> 00:31:53,328
Are you sure you're okay now?

346
00:31:53,912 --> 00:31:55,580
I told you I'm fine.

347
00:31:56,748 --> 00:31:59,042
Shall I call for
the royal physician again?

348
00:32:06,091 --> 00:32:07,092
So…

349
00:32:08,176 --> 00:32:10,804
why did you go see the Queen Mother
as soon as you woke up?

350
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,265
To see Prime Minister Min.

351
00:32:14,724 --> 00:32:15,851
Jeongwoo?

352
00:32:15,934 --> 00:32:18,061
With my waking being uncertain,

353
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:21,857
he would have to find someone
to take my place.

354
00:32:22,566 --> 00:32:23,608
"Take your place"?

355
00:32:27,612 --> 00:32:30,782
Are you saying he asked
the Queen Mother to act as regent?

356
00:32:33,702 --> 00:32:34,828
So did you go there

357
00:32:35,412 --> 00:32:37,539
to show them you're alive and well?

358
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:41,001
Yeah.

359
00:32:44,129 --> 00:32:45,130
Listen.

360
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:47,716
How much

361
00:32:49,384 --> 00:32:50,594
do you trust Jeongwoo?

362
00:32:50,677 --> 00:32:51,970
That's random.

363
00:32:53,096 --> 00:32:54,848
I mean, you two are friends,

364
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,018
but it's so impersonal
between you two sometimes.

365
00:32:58,685 --> 00:33:00,437
Like that time with the contract.

366
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:05,775
There are times I want to punch him.

367
00:33:06,651 --> 00:33:08,195
-What?
-But…

368
00:33:10,030 --> 00:33:11,615
I've always trusted him.

369
00:33:14,242 --> 00:33:15,285
Why?

370
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:17,537
Because I know

371
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:21,791
just as I'm bound by the Crown,
he's bound by the Cabinet.

372
00:33:29,716 --> 00:33:30,717
Why do you ask?

373
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:34,221
Weren't you the one who said it was
only common sense to trust him?

374
00:33:39,643 --> 00:33:40,852
Come here.

375
00:34:00,872 --> 00:34:02,040
There he is!

376
00:34:02,123 --> 00:34:04,751
The arsonist responsible
for the fire at Gyeongbokgung Palace

377
00:34:04,834 --> 00:34:06,044
turned himself in last night.

378
00:34:06,127 --> 00:34:07,754
During questioning, the suspect, Shin,

379
00:34:07,837 --> 00:34:09,923
was identified as a member
of the Royal Guard.

380
00:34:10,006 --> 00:34:11,800
An assassination suspect emerging

381
00:34:11,883 --> 00:34:13,760
from the very force sworn
to protect the Crown

382
00:34:13,843 --> 00:34:15,178
is sending shock waves nationwide.

383
00:34:15,262 --> 00:34:16,638
Remove him!

384
00:34:16,721 --> 00:34:17,847
He was also confirmed

385
00:34:17,931 --> 00:34:20,475
to have protested
for the Grand Prince to step down.

386
00:34:22,185 --> 00:34:23,186
How amusing.

387
00:34:24,312 --> 00:34:25,814
It's as if they timed it to my waking.

388
00:34:28,191 --> 00:34:31,236
Your Majesty,
Grand Prince I-AN has arrived.

389
00:34:31,319 --> 00:34:32,487
Show him in.

390
00:34:36,574 --> 00:34:37,909
Uncle!

391
00:34:41,204 --> 00:34:42,205
Your Majesty.

392
00:34:43,164 --> 00:34:44,541
Are you well?

393
00:34:44,624 --> 00:34:46,751
Yes, that is why I am here.

394
00:34:49,629 --> 00:34:51,840
The fire at the Council Hall…

395
00:35:05,186 --> 00:35:09,232
I thought you would end up like Father…

396
00:35:11,860 --> 00:35:13,528
Do not think such thoughts.

397
00:35:14,988 --> 00:35:16,031
I will

398
00:35:16,531 --> 00:35:18,116
always be by Your Majesty's side.

399
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:36,217
I heard the Grand Prince and Princess
are to resume their public duties.

400
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:38,928
This is their chance.

401
00:35:39,012 --> 00:35:40,513
They will not let it go to waste.

402
00:35:40,597 --> 00:35:43,058
Compassion and pity are but fleeting.

403
00:35:45,226 --> 00:35:47,103
You must stop them from resuming

404
00:35:47,187 --> 00:35:49,064
until that fleeting moment passes.

405
00:35:49,147 --> 00:35:51,441
What makes you think
they will listen to me?

406
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:52,942
Your Majesty!

407
00:35:58,406 --> 00:36:01,284
The Grand Prince nearly lost
his life in a gas explosion.

408
00:36:02,452 --> 00:36:03,995
Use his welfare as grounds

409
00:36:04,079 --> 00:36:06,164
to keep them from resuming their duties.

410
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:13,588
Father.

411
00:36:18,885 --> 00:36:21,471
How did you know the fire was caused

412
00:36:23,139 --> 00:36:24,724
by a gas explosion?

413
00:36:30,313 --> 00:36:32,357
What exactly are you getting at?

414
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,901
That fact was withheld from the public.

415
00:36:38,071 --> 00:36:39,823
So how do you know about that?

416
00:37:23,825 --> 00:37:24,826
Your Majesty.

417
00:37:25,452 --> 00:37:26,745
What is the matter?

418
00:37:28,121 --> 00:37:30,540
Your Majesty, you must steady yourself.

419
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:40,216
It appears I will not
be able to protect you.

420
00:37:45,054 --> 00:37:46,055
Your Majesty…

421
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:49,976
However, I shall see to it…

422
00:37:52,937 --> 00:37:54,439
that your family is kept safe.

423
00:37:57,484 --> 00:37:59,319
Your grace is boundless, Your Majesty.

424
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:12,957
Seriously?

425
00:38:13,541 --> 00:38:16,461
How could one measly royal guard
blow up the Council Hall by himself?

426
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:17,796
My thoughts exactly.

427
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:21,591
The Royal Protection Branch is looking
for accomplices and co-conspirators--

428
00:38:21,674 --> 00:38:23,885
-I need to leave the palace.
-Leave the palace?

429
00:38:31,226 --> 00:38:33,520
Your Royal Highness,
the Queen Mother has arrived.

430
00:38:38,858 --> 00:38:39,859
Show her in.

431
00:38:50,870 --> 00:38:51,871
You may leave.

432
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:07,011
What brings you here?

433
00:39:08,763 --> 00:39:09,931
Your Majesty.

434
00:39:11,224 --> 00:39:12,225
Please stand up.

435
00:39:12,308 --> 00:39:13,309
I have come…

436
00:39:14,727 --> 00:39:16,354
to report a grave offense.

437
00:39:26,573 --> 00:39:27,615
My father…

438
00:39:29,951 --> 00:39:31,953
is trying to kill you.

439
00:39:39,002 --> 00:39:41,588
This is the evidence
from the incident on your wedding day.

440
00:39:51,806 --> 00:39:53,683
LEE AREUM

441
00:39:53,766 --> 00:39:56,519
I also have the girl who used to work
at your private residence.

442
00:39:57,186 --> 00:39:58,563
She has sworn to testify.

443
00:40:03,192 --> 00:40:05,069
What is your intent in reporting this?

444
00:40:06,988 --> 00:40:08,364
The recent fire…

445
00:40:12,327 --> 00:40:14,162
It was likely my father's doing.

446
00:40:16,456 --> 00:40:17,582
So?

447
00:40:18,666 --> 00:40:20,001
Are you here to beg

448
00:40:21,044 --> 00:40:22,086
for his forgiveness?

449
00:40:22,170 --> 00:40:23,796
I am asking you to exact punishment.

450
00:40:26,466 --> 00:40:27,759
Punish me…

451
00:40:31,512 --> 00:40:32,639
and my father.

452
00:40:48,321 --> 00:40:49,989
Did you believe me incapable of it?

453
00:40:51,157 --> 00:40:52,575
And should I choose to do so…

454
00:40:54,744 --> 00:40:56,371
are you sure you can handle it?

455
00:41:06,714 --> 00:41:07,966
I shall try.

456
00:41:25,149 --> 00:41:26,609
It's almost hunting season.

457
00:41:27,735 --> 00:41:30,446
Right, since harvest season is
just around the corner.

458
00:41:30,530 --> 00:41:33,992
Tell them I will be declaring
hunting season this year.

459
00:41:35,368 --> 00:41:36,494
And not the royal family?

460
00:41:38,955 --> 00:41:40,748
The Grand Prince needs time to recover,

461
00:41:42,041 --> 00:41:44,419
and the Queen Mother
does not appreciate hunting.

462
00:41:46,337 --> 00:41:47,922
Then I'll do it.

463
00:41:50,842 --> 00:41:51,843
I guess I can do it.

464
00:42:01,644 --> 00:42:03,563
Is it because I am accepting
the royal edict?

465
00:42:05,815 --> 00:42:06,816
Why?

466
00:42:10,486 --> 00:42:11,821
Why do you fear me now?

467
00:42:17,785 --> 00:42:19,579
It is not that I fear you.

468
00:42:26,127 --> 00:42:27,128
I have…

469
00:42:31,257 --> 00:42:33,301
a duty to protect the Crown.

470
00:42:36,054 --> 00:42:37,764
Thus, I am protecting you.

471
00:42:38,765 --> 00:42:41,225
I am ensuring that neither my father
nor my own greed

472
00:42:42,351 --> 00:42:44,520
ever harm you or the Crown again.

473
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,566
So please…

474
00:42:57,825 --> 00:42:58,868
Just spare…

475
00:43:01,120 --> 00:43:02,288
His Majesty.

476
00:43:14,967 --> 00:43:16,469
As great as the honor once was…

477
00:43:18,763 --> 00:43:20,306
so too shall your disgrace be.

478
00:43:22,767 --> 00:43:24,393
In both the royal family and history,

479
00:43:25,770 --> 00:43:27,396
you will forever remain a sinner.

480
00:43:32,568 --> 00:43:34,403
If that is the price to spare His Majesty…

481
00:43:40,326 --> 00:43:41,452
would you accept?

482
00:43:48,126 --> 00:43:49,335
It is more than enough.

483
00:44:11,065 --> 00:44:12,859
But…

484
00:44:13,651 --> 00:44:15,778
"hunting season" in the 21st century?

485
00:44:16,821 --> 00:44:18,030
What about animal rights?

486
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:22,118
Think of it as a necessary evil.

487
00:44:24,287 --> 00:44:25,872
When harmful entities multiply…

488
00:44:28,791 --> 00:44:30,334
we can't protect what matters.

489
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:33,796
And who determines that?

490
00:44:36,215 --> 00:44:37,383
The Crown?

491
00:44:42,263 --> 00:44:43,264
The nation.

492
00:44:47,310 --> 00:44:48,311
I see.

493
00:45:01,449 --> 00:45:03,201
So, you decide.

494
00:45:30,228 --> 00:45:31,395
I saw you caught the guy.

495
00:45:32,605 --> 00:45:34,315
Was he a harmful entity too?

496
00:46:04,387 --> 00:46:06,681
Hey. I'm on my way back.

497
00:46:08,557 --> 00:46:09,558
You're where?

498
00:46:19,110 --> 00:46:20,736
He's a little drunk.

499
00:46:21,612 --> 00:46:22,655
He's drunk?

500
00:46:22,738 --> 00:46:26,575
Gosh. He can't even hold his liquor…

501
00:46:30,538 --> 00:46:33,332
Boy, I'm tired. Who wants coffee?

502
00:46:33,416 --> 00:46:34,417
Me.

503
00:46:53,728 --> 00:46:54,895
Your Royal Highness.

504
00:46:55,980 --> 00:46:58,149
My dear wife.

505
00:47:03,612 --> 00:47:06,449
This is great.
I was feeling cooped up anyway.

506
00:47:06,949 --> 00:47:08,909
You were?

507
00:47:08,993 --> 00:47:09,994
Yeah.

508
00:47:10,536 --> 00:47:12,371
The palace is so much bigger,

509
00:47:13,122 --> 00:47:14,290
but far more stifling.

510
00:47:16,292 --> 00:47:18,127
Agreed.

511
00:47:28,471 --> 00:47:30,222
The Queen Mother came to see me earlier.

512
00:47:37,813 --> 00:47:39,315
She told me Lord INPYEONG…

513
00:47:45,654 --> 00:47:47,073
was behind the wedding incident.

514
00:47:57,833 --> 00:48:00,044
Seeing her beg so desperately
to spare His Majesty…

515
00:48:07,009 --> 00:48:08,469
I no longer know what I am to do.

516
00:48:33,244 --> 00:48:34,954
You have such a gentle heart.

517
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:37,998
It breaks my heart.

518
00:48:54,390 --> 00:48:55,850
THE THIRTY-THIRD KING

519
00:48:57,226 --> 00:48:59,937
It will reach him this time, won't it?

520
00:49:01,772 --> 00:49:03,065
I believe so.

521
00:49:06,444 --> 00:49:07,736
I shall entrust it to you.

522
00:49:09,196 --> 00:49:11,031
Rest assured, Your Majesty.

523
00:49:28,424 --> 00:49:29,758
I heard you asked for me.

524
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:36,223
I wanted to commend you
for your swift arrest

525
00:49:37,183 --> 00:49:38,851
of the arsonist.

526
00:49:41,854 --> 00:49:43,230
The police deserve the credit.

527
00:49:44,565 --> 00:49:47,526
I am well aware that nothing in this realm

528
00:49:48,235 --> 00:49:49,236
is beyond your reach.

529
00:49:52,865 --> 00:49:53,866
However,

530
00:49:55,743 --> 00:49:57,495
are you still far from concluding

531
00:50:00,706 --> 00:50:01,832
the poisoning case?

532
00:50:06,545 --> 00:50:08,214
Hmm…

533
00:50:15,888 --> 00:50:17,097
It won't be long now.

534
00:50:29,193 --> 00:50:30,736
Lord INPYEONG of the Yun Family.

535
00:50:34,156 --> 00:50:35,407
He is the culprit.

536
00:50:36,325 --> 00:50:37,326
In terms of punishment,

537
00:50:38,327 --> 00:50:39,453
I'm still deliberating.

538
00:50:43,499 --> 00:50:44,792
About Prime Minister Min…

539
00:50:49,004 --> 00:50:50,130
Be wary of him.

540
00:50:53,509 --> 00:50:54,552
What does that mean?

541
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:58,556
He was the first
to discover my father's crimes.

542
00:51:02,643 --> 00:51:04,770
-That is not possible.
-He knew everything,

543
00:51:05,312 --> 00:51:07,314
but chose to keep it from you.

544
00:51:07,398 --> 00:51:09,108
He would have no reason to do that.

545
00:51:10,818 --> 00:51:12,653
Do you truly believe that?

546
00:51:14,655 --> 00:51:15,823
How much

547
00:51:16,824 --> 00:51:18,033
do you trust Jeongwoo?

548
00:51:21,579 --> 00:51:24,790
Those driven by desperate desire…

549
00:51:29,086 --> 00:51:31,380
often resort to unseemly choices.

550
00:51:45,060 --> 00:51:46,604
What is there to consider?

551
00:51:48,314 --> 00:51:50,566
As someone who is concerned
for the Crown's welfare,

552
00:51:50,649 --> 00:51:51,942
I have much to consider.

553
00:51:52,610 --> 00:51:54,320
He tried to kill me.

554
00:51:54,403 --> 00:51:56,071
He's also the Queen Mother's father.

555
00:51:56,155 --> 00:51:58,574
-Prime Minister Min.
-And His Majesty's grandfather.

556
00:51:58,657 --> 00:52:00,409
-Min Jeongwoo.
-Please!

557
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:12,671
Stop acting like a child.

558
00:52:22,765 --> 00:52:24,350
Lord INPYEONG will…

559
00:52:25,351 --> 00:52:26,935
…never set foot in this realm again.

560
00:52:27,019 --> 00:52:28,020
He will…

561
00:52:31,690 --> 00:52:33,317
carry out his sentence in this realm.

562
00:52:35,152 --> 00:52:37,029
Do you wish to see the Crown crumble?

563
00:52:37,112 --> 00:52:39,031
Is there any reason why it should not?

564
00:52:47,873 --> 00:52:48,874
The Crown…

565
00:52:51,543 --> 00:52:52,795
cannot last forever.

566
00:52:57,549 --> 00:52:58,842
Once I ascend the throne,

567
00:53:00,511 --> 00:53:02,012
I will abolish the monarchy.

568
00:53:21,365 --> 00:53:23,617
You've attained
everything you ever wanted.

569
00:53:25,786 --> 00:53:27,663
And now you seek freedom as well?

570
00:53:32,501 --> 00:53:33,502
This freedom…

571
00:53:35,295 --> 00:53:36,296
won't be mine alone.

572
00:54:16,378 --> 00:54:17,379
Are you okay?

573
00:54:22,009 --> 00:54:23,594
Lord INPYEONG will be arrested soon.

574
00:54:27,139 --> 00:54:28,140
Did Jeongwoo

575
00:54:29,099 --> 00:54:30,142
agree to it?

576
00:54:31,226 --> 00:54:32,227
No.

577
00:54:33,979 --> 00:54:35,355
But he'll have no other choice.

578
00:54:36,356 --> 00:54:37,566
I told him I knew…

579
00:54:39,485 --> 00:54:41,028
and that I would not forgive him.

580
00:54:54,124 --> 00:54:55,709
And what you wanted to confirm?

581
00:54:56,627 --> 00:54:57,628
Did you?

582
00:55:03,967 --> 00:55:04,968
No.

583
00:55:43,215 --> 00:55:45,342
The first-ever compulsory investigation

584
00:55:45,425 --> 00:55:47,052
into a royal relative has been conducted.

585
00:55:47,135 --> 00:55:50,305
The Royal Protection Branch and police
announced they have obtained evidence

586
00:55:50,389 --> 00:55:53,767
that proves Lord INPYEONG's involvement
in Grand Princess Seong's poisoning.

587
00:55:53,850 --> 00:55:56,520
Authorities raided his home
and a research facility affiliated

588
00:55:56,603 --> 00:55:57,938
with the Royal Seoul Hospital.

589
00:55:58,021 --> 00:55:59,523
ROYAL PROTECTION BRANCH

590
00:55:59,606 --> 00:56:01,108
-Look!
-There she is!

591
00:56:01,191 --> 00:56:04,069
The joint investigation task
force stated shipment records of a drug

592
00:56:04,152 --> 00:56:06,863
containing the same substance
administered to the Grand Prince,

593
00:56:06,947 --> 00:56:10,617
as well as a testimony from a staff member
at his private residence, proved decisive.

594
00:56:10,701 --> 00:56:13,996
With a royal relative suspected
in an attempted murder of a royal,

595
00:56:14,079 --> 00:56:16,164
the fallout is expected to be significant.

596
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:26,466
Your Majesty.

597
00:56:27,342 --> 00:56:29,011
His Majesty has arrived.

598
00:56:35,517 --> 00:56:36,685
Mother.

599
00:56:45,277 --> 00:56:46,278
Your Majesty.

600
00:56:47,362 --> 00:56:48,363
Yes?

601
00:56:53,744 --> 00:56:55,454
You must remain strong.

602
00:56:58,415 --> 00:56:59,583
If you ever feel scared,

603
00:57:00,751 --> 00:57:02,711
you should go to your uncle.

604
00:57:04,379 --> 00:57:05,756
Do you understand?

605
00:57:07,215 --> 00:57:09,468
Yes, Mother.

606
00:57:33,617 --> 00:57:34,910
Your Royal Highness.

607
00:57:35,577 --> 00:57:37,329
This is a misunderstanding.

608
00:57:37,412 --> 00:57:39,206
Why would I ever…

609
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:40,290
Shut…

610
00:57:43,293 --> 00:57:44,294
that mouth of yours.

611
00:57:47,422 --> 00:57:49,508
History will remember you as a criminal,

612
00:57:50,258 --> 00:57:51,259
and the Crown

613
00:57:52,761 --> 00:57:54,054
will forget you ever existed.

614
00:57:56,056 --> 00:57:59,267
I am His Majesty's grandfather
and the Queen Mother's father.

615
00:57:59,935 --> 00:58:01,144
You cannot treat me like--

616
00:58:01,228 --> 00:58:02,270
Did I not ask you…

617
00:58:04,564 --> 00:58:06,274
to shut that mouth of yours?

618
00:58:11,947 --> 00:58:13,699
The Queen Mother was the one

619
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:16,326
who told me about your crimes.

620
00:58:19,955 --> 00:58:20,956
Thus…

621
00:58:23,083 --> 00:58:24,543
you should mind your conduct.

622
00:58:28,755 --> 00:58:30,340
The Queen Mother's welfare…

623
00:58:32,884 --> 00:58:34,803
will depend on how deeply…

624
00:58:38,181 --> 00:58:39,349
you repent.

625
00:59:00,579 --> 00:59:02,080
You did well, Your Royal Highness.

626
00:59:06,918 --> 00:59:08,670
The abdication has been announced.

627
00:59:09,546 --> 00:59:12,048
Public sentiment is strong,
and the foreign media is all over it,

628
00:59:12,132 --> 00:59:13,258
calling it long overdue.

629
00:59:13,842 --> 00:59:16,386
-Let's go to the palace.
-Yes, Your Royal Highness.

630
00:59:16,470 --> 00:59:17,971
Abolition?

631
00:59:18,054 --> 00:59:21,183
How dare anyone suggest
to abolish the monarchy?

632
00:59:21,266 --> 00:59:25,645
Why do we spend all that tax money
preserving the Crown?

633
00:59:25,729 --> 00:59:28,815
Because the investment generates
enough added value to justify the cost.

634
00:59:28,899 --> 00:59:32,152
If the economic and diplomatic benefits
of the Crown vanish,

635
00:59:32,235 --> 00:59:35,238
who exactly will be held accountable?

636
00:59:35,322 --> 00:59:37,908
The people will be up in arms about it.

637
00:59:37,991 --> 00:59:39,826
I'm sure such news will have them

638
00:59:39,910 --> 00:59:41,453
demanding a new king immediately.

639
00:59:45,791 --> 00:59:47,626
That is exactly why…

640
00:59:51,671 --> 00:59:53,340
…we must make him listen.

641
01:00:26,164 --> 01:00:27,874
You must be busy with the coronation.

642
01:00:28,959 --> 01:00:30,293
The Grand Prince told me.

643
01:00:38,468 --> 01:00:39,970
That you had been aware

644
01:00:42,013 --> 01:00:43,306
of what Lord INPYEONG did.

645
01:00:50,021 --> 01:00:51,106
Then what about you?

646
01:00:52,148 --> 01:00:53,567
Did you know?

647
01:00:53,650 --> 01:00:55,777
That he's looking to abolish the monarchy.

648
01:01:00,031 --> 01:01:01,032
A king

649
01:01:02,117 --> 01:01:04,327
doesn't get to do whatever he wants.

650
01:01:05,036 --> 01:01:06,830
My job is to make sure he doesn't.

651
01:01:06,913 --> 01:01:08,331
What if it is a necessary evil?

652
01:01:08,415 --> 01:01:09,624
What?

653
01:01:09,708 --> 01:01:12,794
What if, in the 21st century,
our Crown itself turns out to be

654
01:01:14,045 --> 01:01:15,171
the harmful entity?

655
01:01:17,424 --> 01:01:18,550
What then?

656
01:01:25,849 --> 01:01:26,933
I already told you.

657
01:01:28,059 --> 01:01:30,228
That is for the nation to decide.

658
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:40,238
It appears…

659
01:01:46,620 --> 01:01:48,121
we may end up as enemies.

660
01:02:07,140 --> 01:02:10,727
Announcing His Majesty!

661
01:03:17,919 --> 01:03:20,463
We declare!

662
01:03:20,547 --> 01:03:22,340
-Long live the King!
-Long live the King!

663
01:03:25,176 --> 01:03:27,721
-Long live the King!
-Long live the King!

664
01:03:29,848 --> 01:03:32,434
-Long live the King!
-Long live the King!

665
01:03:48,533 --> 01:03:51,453
PERFECT CROWN

666
01:04:28,615 --> 01:04:30,867
All rise
for His Majesty the King!

667
01:04:30,950 --> 01:04:33,036
Your Majesty.
Abolition of the monarchy?

668
01:04:33,119 --> 01:04:35,246
Is it true there are talks
of abolishing the monarchy?

669
01:04:35,330 --> 01:04:37,082
You're saying the Cabinet
and Royal Relatives

670
01:04:37,165 --> 01:04:38,625
will oppose it, no question?

671
01:04:38,708 --> 01:04:42,128
Most of the establishment
is connected to the Crown.

672
01:04:42,212 --> 01:04:43,797
Voice your objection there.

673
01:04:45,256 --> 01:04:46,549
Simply hint that…

674
01:04:46,633 --> 01:04:48,551
…is His Majesty's own pursuit.

675
01:04:48,635 --> 01:04:49,719
What summons?

676
01:04:49,803 --> 01:04:51,554
It's a slush fund probe.

677
01:04:51,638 --> 01:04:55,183
And the Cabinet implored me
to fulfill my duties as the King.

678
01:04:55,266 --> 01:04:57,227
We were simply speaking
on behalf of the public.

679
01:04:57,310 --> 01:04:59,479
Go and protect His Majesty.

680
01:04:59,562 --> 01:05:00,730
It's your fault.

681
01:05:03,066 --> 01:05:05,068
Translated by Justin S. Kim.

682
01:05:16,371 --> 01:05:20,083
PERFECT CROWN
